<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

00:29.714 --> 00:31.615
♪ ♪

00:31.674 --> 00:33.975
LISA:
<i>Our Lord, Buddha, says,</i>

00:34.010 --> 00:37.279
<i>"The secret of existence</i>
<i>is to pass beyond fear."</i>

00:37.313 --> 00:39.848
<i>My brother is about</i>
<i>to meet fear...</i>

00:39.882 --> 00:41.082
<i>and as usual...</i>

00:41.117 --> 00:42.651
<i>he won't pass.</i>

00:45.988 --> 00:47.822
Wake up, Lis!
It's the last day of school!

00:47.857 --> 00:49.257
(groans)

00:49.292 --> 00:50.292
Wake up, Maggs!

00:50.326 --> 00:51.626
It's the last day of school!

00:51.661 --> 00:53.361
(singsongy):
Last day of school!

00:53.396 --> 00:54.796
(metal clanging rhythmically)
Last day of school!

00:54.830 --> 00:56.565
Found my summer hobby!

00:56.599 --> 00:57.933
Banging pots together!

00:57.967 --> 00:58.934
Don't worry, Marge.

00:58.968 --> 01:00.202
As a favor to you,

01:00.236 --> 01:02.270
I'm enrolling
that precious little jerk

01:02.305 --> 01:05.239
in this fresh air summer camp.

01:06.609 --> 01:08.143
That's a prison road crew.

01:08.177 --> 01:09.744
I did that last summer.

01:09.779 --> 01:10.745
I'm not allowed back.

01:10.780 --> 01:12.581
(humming)

01:12.615 --> 01:13.815
(whirring)

01:13.849 --> 01:16.084
Good-bye forever,
multiplication!

01:17.286 --> 01:18.720
(slurps)

01:18.754 --> 01:19.721
Uh...

01:19.755 --> 01:20.822
needs more numerators.

01:22.692 --> 01:24.192
Ah, "July 4th..."

01:24.227 --> 01:25.293
What the...?

01:25.328 --> 01:26.928
No fireworks?!

01:26.963 --> 01:30.565
Can't this stupid city
entertain me one night a year?!

01:30.600 --> 01:32.234
The city's broke.

01:32.268 --> 01:34.069
The fire department
has to raise money

01:34.103 --> 01:35.604
by delivering pizza.

01:38.107 --> 01:40.408
My baby!

01:40.443 --> 01:42.010
Back ribs!

01:42.044 --> 01:43.511
Marge, when you're broke,

01:43.546 --> 01:45.780
that's when you got to
keep up appearances.

01:45.815 --> 01:48.750
The Fourth of July is the one
day a year when our city puts on

01:48.784 --> 01:50.252
her high heels and tube top

01:50.286 --> 01:52.854
and leans into
America's car window.

01:52.888 --> 01:54.956
(crying):
God bless her.

01:56.292 --> 01:58.093
LISA:
<i>The last day of school.</i>

01:58.127 --> 01:59.761
<i>Field Day.</i>

01:59.795 --> 02:02.063
<i>When you learn to balance</i>
<i>an egg on a spoon</i>

02:02.098 --> 02:03.898
<i>and run with</i>
<i>your leg tied to someone</i>

02:03.933 --> 02:05.800
<i>who wouldn't</i>
<i>talk to you all year.</i>

02:05.835 --> 02:09.104
Hey! Are you coming to the
after-school pool party?

02:09.138 --> 02:11.239
Not now.

02:11.274 --> 02:13.908
(giggles)

02:13.943 --> 02:15.977
Aw... no fair!

02:16.012 --> 02:18.313
He actually has
three legs.

02:18.347 --> 02:20.148
You lay off
my son Tripod!

02:20.182 --> 02:22.250
He won fair and square,

02:22.285 --> 02:26.087
just like my twins
Wheel and Barrow.

02:26.122 --> 02:28.790
Now, take you brother
to the face painting.

02:28.824 --> 02:31.760
But don't make yourselves up
to look all freaky.

02:31.794 --> 02:34.496
One, two, three, toss.

02:34.530 --> 02:36.698
(laughs)

02:36.732 --> 02:39.167
The eggs are supposed
to be tossed between students,

02:39.201 --> 02:40.835
not <i>at</i> the principal.

02:40.870 --> 02:43.471
Once more and hurl!
Aah!

02:43.506 --> 02:46.775
We will do this
until we get it right.

02:46.809 --> 02:50.578
Look, do you want this to be
your last school memory?

02:50.580 --> 02:51.746
(groans)

02:51.781 --> 02:53.948
Pull harder!

02:53.983 --> 02:55.350
What is wrong with you people?!

02:55.384 --> 02:56.484
Hey.

02:56.519 --> 02:59.254
I have thumbs, too.

02:59.288 --> 03:02.991
(chiming)

03:03.025 --> 03:04.993
(yells)

03:06.862 --> 03:09.831
I like the Play-Doh
that comes out the back.

03:10.833 --> 03:13.335
See you next June, Macaroni.

03:13.369 --> 03:15.704
(door latch slides shut)

03:20.509 --> 03:24.713
And now the climactic
Race around the School.

03:24.747 --> 03:26.114
Previous winners include

03:26.148 --> 03:27.215
Sideshow Mel,

03:27.249 --> 03:28.783
Señora Bumblebee Man

03:28.818 --> 03:31.720
and Olympian Edwin Moses.

03:31.754 --> 03:32.887
I'll bet your
biggest hurdle was

03:32.922 --> 03:34.489
leaving your
beloved hometown.

03:34.523 --> 03:36.324
All hurdles
are the same size.

03:36.359 --> 03:38.059
Man... who is this loser?

03:38.094 --> 03:40.061
I've got a secret, Bart.

03:40.096 --> 03:41.363
That's good.

03:41.397 --> 03:42.797
Want to know what it is?

03:42.832 --> 03:43.998
No.

03:44.033 --> 03:45.233
My secret is

03:45.267 --> 03:46.835
I've been training
for this race

03:46.869 --> 03:48.336
and no one suspects.

03:48.371 --> 03:49.404
Check it out:

03:49.438 --> 03:51.239
I'm wearing a dummy tummy.

03:52.942 --> 03:54.142
I'm gonna win

03:54.176 --> 03:56.244
and it'll change my life!

03:58.614 --> 03:59.914
Wow!

03:59.949 --> 04:02.217
Breaking that tape
cured your asthma.

04:02.251 --> 04:03.251
(deep voice):
Marvelous!

04:03.285 --> 04:04.586
Ha-ha-ha!

04:04.620 --> 04:07.255
(guffaws)

04:07.289 --> 04:08.590
(gasps)

04:11.894 --> 04:14.062
(lisping):
Six on Bart Simpson.

04:14.096 --> 04:16.096
BOTH:
Two on us to win.

04:16.132 --> 04:17.699
$20 on Milhouse.

04:17.733 --> 04:19.334
Milhouse?!
(scoffs)

04:19.368 --> 04:21.435
That's a thousand-to-one odds.

04:21.470 --> 04:23.905
Perhaps I should
take my action to Willie.

04:23.939 --> 04:25.707
(grunts)
I ain't makin' book no more.

04:25.741 --> 04:27.175
I lost the deed to my shack!

04:27.209 --> 04:29.110
You are late
with the rent, Willie.

04:29.145 --> 04:31.112
I'll have it by Friday, Mr. U.

04:31.147 --> 04:32.614
I swear.

04:32.648 --> 04:33.915
We can handle your action.

04:33.949 --> 04:35.717
(trumpet playing
in the distance)

04:35.751 --> 04:38.119
Betting is now closed.

04:40.256 --> 04:41.556
(panting)

04:41.590 --> 04:43.792
And now, the 79th running

04:43.826 --> 04:46.428
of the Race around the School.

04:46.462 --> 04:48.163
Gun in the school!

04:48.197 --> 04:49.631
What the...?

04:49.665 --> 04:53.034
Just, just go.
And they're off!

04:53.068 --> 04:54.936
We've got a pack of
fifth-graders on the rail,

04:54.970 --> 04:57.238
Simp-son holding down the center

04:57.273 --> 05:00.708
while Database and Cosine are
still testing the wind speed.

05:00.743 --> 05:02.444
As the runners go
into the first turn,

05:02.478 --> 05:03.812
Lewis is in the lead!

05:03.846 --> 05:05.280
Followed by Lovejoy's daughter,

05:05.314 --> 05:06.414
Fat Tony's nephew,

05:06.449 --> 05:07.615
Brockman's little girl...
(screams)

05:07.650 --> 05:09.217
...and Jailbird's kid!

05:09.251 --> 05:10.552
The Frank Sinatra kid...

05:10.586 --> 05:12.387
well, he's doing it his way!

05:12.421 --> 05:15.657
Rounding out the pack are all
the kids that we never see.

05:15.691 --> 05:17.125
What's this?

05:17.159 --> 05:19.060
Milhouse takes the lead?

05:19.094 --> 05:20.574
The same boy
who sprained his shoulder

05:20.596 --> 05:22.330
doing the Pledge of Allegiance?

05:22.364 --> 05:23.765
(panting)

05:23.799 --> 05:25.433
Uh-oh!
If Milhouse wins this race,

05:25.468 --> 05:26.901
we're out a fortune.

05:26.936 --> 05:28.770
Don't worry.
The race takes a turn

05:28.804 --> 05:30.605
through the trees
where no one can see.

05:30.639 --> 05:32.974
When Milhouse gets there,
you know what to do.

05:33.008 --> 05:35.076
Oh, yeah. Totally.

05:35.110 --> 05:37.111
I mean, it's so obvious.

05:37.146 --> 05:38.480
Just punch him!

05:38.514 --> 05:40.014
Exactly.

05:40.049 --> 05:43.318
Right in the nnn...
fff... dee...?

05:43.352 --> 05:45.753
There is no wrong answer!

05:45.788 --> 05:47.755
CHALMERS: And Milhouse,
the boy nobody loves,

05:47.790 --> 05:49.824
is widening his lead!

05:49.859 --> 05:51.326
And what does he have
to jump over?

05:51.360 --> 05:52.694
Nothing, that's what.

05:52.728 --> 05:54.262
I'm out of here.

05:54.296 --> 05:56.764
(grunting)

05:56.799 --> 05:58.800
Good job, Edwin.

06:00.169 --> 06:01.803
I'm doing it! I'm doing it!

06:01.837 --> 06:04.272
And when I win,
I'm changing my name.

06:04.306 --> 06:07.141
To something cool like Winnie!

06:09.812 --> 06:12.881
Did you come to give
me a cup of water?

06:13.916 --> 06:15.350
(both grunt)

06:15.384 --> 06:17.785
The best day of my life

06:17.820 --> 06:20.822
just turned into every
other day of my life.

06:23.826 --> 06:25.693
LISA:
<i>Bart faced a terrible choice--</i>

06:25.728 --> 06:27.529
<i>take a beating with his friend</i>

06:27.563 --> 06:29.731
<i>or slither off like a coward.</i>

06:29.765 --> 06:32.166
<i>And like he did with every</i>
<i>multiple choice question</i>

06:32.201 --> 06:36.070
<i>he ever saw, Bart chose "B."</i>

06:42.244 --> 06:44.646
(crowd cheering)

06:44.680 --> 06:46.981
The winner is Bart Simpson!

06:47.016 --> 06:48.516
LISA:
<i>Bart won a blue ribbon.</i>

06:48.551 --> 06:49.717
<i>But was it worth it?</i>

06:49.752 --> 06:51.719
MARGE:
<i>Lisa! Bath time!</i>

06:51.754 --> 06:53.922
LISA:
<i>Mom! I'm narrating!</i>

06:53.956 --> 06:55.823
MARGE:
<i>The water's gonna get cold!</i>

06:55.858 --> 06:57.392
LISA:
<i>Fine.</i>

07:01.551 --> 07:04.779
[]LISA: <i>As the pin on the back</i>
<i>of the blue ribbon made its way</i>

07:04.780 --> 07:06.747
<i>through Bart's shirt</i>
<i>and into its housing,</i>

07:06.782 --> 07:08.749
<i>the seeds of his comeuppance</i>

07:08.784 --> 07:10.751
<i>flew out of the woods.</i>

07:10.786 --> 07:12.720
Son! What happened to you

07:12.754 --> 07:15.122
in the dark place
behind the school?

07:15.157 --> 07:16.490
Something good?

07:18.160 --> 07:20.728
I'm afraid I don't remember.

07:20.762 --> 07:22.363
Whew.

07:22.397 --> 07:24.397
Well, it looks like Milhouse
has traumatic amnesia.

07:24.399 --> 07:26.233
He may never remember
what happened to him.

07:26.268 --> 07:29.971
The most important thing is, the
race results are now official.

07:30.005 --> 07:31.839
Now I've got to look
at some severe cases

07:31.873 --> 07:34.642
of ice cream headache.

07:34.676 --> 07:36.644
(theme from <i>MASH</i> playing)

07:38.000 --> 07:44.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:47.689 --> 07:49.957
(Bart groaning)

07:51.994 --> 07:53.794
(gasps)

07:53.829 --> 07:55.763
Help me, Bart!

07:57.532 --> 07:58.899
(screams)

07:58.934 --> 08:00.735
Help me, Bart!

08:00.769 --> 08:01.969
(shouts)

08:02.004 --> 08:03.270
(gasps)

08:03.305 --> 08:05.740
Help me, Bart!

08:07.843 --> 08:08.943
(gasping)

08:08.977 --> 08:10.578
Why am I having nightmares?

08:10.612 --> 08:11.946
I'm no coward.

08:11.980 --> 08:13.047
(screams)

08:13.081 --> 08:14.215
A chicken feather?

08:14.249 --> 08:15.750
Why would you hand this to me?

08:15.784 --> 08:17.451
Oh, you must've figured out

08:17.486 --> 08:19.286
I chickened out during the race.

08:19.321 --> 08:21.789
Well, who are you to judge me?

08:22.824 --> 08:24.892
I suck? You suck!

08:24.926 --> 08:27.561
LISA: <i>While Bart was being</i>
<i>outwitted by a baby,</i>

08:27.596 --> 08:31.399
<i>something was coming to a boil</i>
<i>in our pop's brainpan.</i>

08:31.433 --> 08:34.467
Marge, if this stupid,
one-reactor town won't put on

08:34.503 --> 08:36.136
a fireworks show, I will.

08:36.171 --> 08:37.738
I've mapped it out.

08:37.773 --> 08:39.506
(laughs)
Hmm?

08:39.541 --> 08:41.808
(groans)

08:41.842 --> 08:45.746
Maybe we should just light
sparklers in the backyard.

08:45.781 --> 08:49.183
Eh, I've had my problems
with sparklers.

08:49.217 --> 08:50.918
Fun! Fun! Fun! Fun! Fun!
Fun! Fun! Fun!

08:50.952 --> 08:52.486
(screams)

08:52.521 --> 08:54.488
LISA:
<i>But Fourth of July fireworks</i>

08:54.523 --> 08:55.690
<i>were a different story.</i>

08:55.724 --> 08:57.291
<i>They meant more to my dad</i>

08:57.325 --> 08:59.126
<i>than my Mom could ever know.</i>

08:59.161 --> 09:01.195
<i>It was the one night</i>
<i>of every year</i>

09:01.229 --> 09:03.764
<i>that he couldn't hear</i>
<i>his parents argue.</i>

09:03.799 --> 09:06.367
<i>He figured it was because</i>
<i>they loved the fireworks</i>

09:06.401 --> 09:08.436
<i>just as much as he did.</i>

09:08.470 --> 09:10.504
I want to take a class!

09:10.539 --> 09:13.874
Why can't you be happy
ironing my shirts?!

09:13.909 --> 09:15.476
I need space!

09:15.510 --> 09:18.913
Then close your eyes
and go to Hawaii!

09:18.947 --> 09:22.116
LISA: <i>With his mom gone,</i>
<i>Homer needed a hero,</i>

09:22.150 --> 09:25.186
<i>and no one was a bigger hero</i>

09:25.220 --> 09:26.854
<i>than the magical little man</i>

09:26.888 --> 09:27.888
<i>behind the controls.</i>

09:27.923 --> 09:29.390
(fireworks whistling)

09:29.424 --> 09:30.958
Are you God?

09:30.992 --> 09:32.793
No, no.

09:32.828 --> 09:36.330
But I shoot rockets
into his a-face.

09:36.364 --> 09:37.865
Here's-a my card.

09:37.899 --> 09:41.502
Don't forget to treasure it.

09:41.536 --> 09:43.471
Hmm.

09:43.505 --> 09:44.672
Now let's see.

09:44.706 --> 09:46.373
Which pants have that card?

09:46.408 --> 09:48.309
Board shorts, interested shorts.

09:48.343 --> 09:50.845
Here we are.

09:50.879 --> 09:52.780
Kaboom.

09:54.282 --> 09:57.017
Giuseppe, I want you
to come out of retirement

09:57.052 --> 10:00.020
for the greatest fireworks show
of your career.

10:00.055 --> 10:03.057
Why do you come here and remind
me of a time in my life

10:03.091 --> 10:06.827
when I made a-tons of money
doing a-what I love?

10:06.862 --> 10:09.230
If the <i>Expendables</i> movies
have taught us anything,

10:09.264 --> 10:11.432
it's that people
do their best work

10:11.466 --> 10:13.834
after they're old
and forgotten.

10:13.869 --> 10:17.772
Well, I am younger
than Sylvester Stallone.

10:17.806 --> 10:19.640
I will do it!

10:23.779 --> 10:25.079
Hey, buddy.

10:25.113 --> 10:27.681
Bart, my truest friend.

10:27.716 --> 10:29.150
I brought you a cake.

10:29.184 --> 10:30.718
Read it.

10:30.752 --> 10:32.620
That's an odd message.

10:32.654 --> 10:34.789
But who am I to
argue with icing?

10:34.823 --> 10:37.758
Will you watch <i>Cassidy</i>
<i>the Crocodile</i> with me?

10:37.793 --> 10:40.528
Um, that's kind
of a baby show.

10:40.562 --> 10:42.196
It's all I can handle now.

10:42.230 --> 10:45.599
(sighs)

10:45.634 --> 10:47.134
Henrietta Kitten?

10:47.169 --> 10:48.769
Will you marry me?

10:48.804 --> 10:50.771
Meow, meow, maybe.

10:50.806 --> 10:52.439
Why would a kitten
marry a crocodile?

10:52.474 --> 10:53.741
Wouldn't it eat her?

10:53.775 --> 10:54.875
(shushes)

10:54.910 --> 10:57.311
Suspension of disbelief.

10:57.345 --> 11:00.147
Friends help
friends in trouble.

11:00.182 --> 11:01.148
No! Turn it off!

11:01.183 --> 11:02.883
It's too intense for me!

11:02.918 --> 11:06.387
Some guys just can't
handle crocodiles.

11:06.421 --> 11:07.922
Is it over yet?

11:07.956 --> 11:09.256
(chicken clucks)

11:09.291 --> 11:10.457
And if you're dissatisfied

11:10.492 --> 11:11.892
for any reason,

11:11.927 --> 11:13.594
I will refund your money

11:13.628 --> 11:15.763
in the form of acorns.

11:18.433 --> 11:20.067
(groans)

11:20.101 --> 11:23.771
Hey, this gunpowder,
it has a-crystal meth in it.

11:23.805 --> 11:25.573
Crystal meth?
Then what the heck

11:25.607 --> 11:28.342
did I sell
to them Colombian drug lords?

11:29.644 --> 11:30.978
Brandine!

11:31.012 --> 11:33.914
We're feuding
with the Escobars again!

11:33.949 --> 11:36.617
Does that mean
I ain't talking to Maria?

11:36.651 --> 11:38.452
Duh! Yes.

11:38.486 --> 11:39.520
Homer, we will get

11:39.554 --> 11:42.523
the fireworks someplace else.

11:42.557 --> 11:45.860
The pig's been eating
the C-4 blocks again!

11:45.894 --> 11:48.028
(burps)

11:48.063 --> 11:50.364
(dog barks)

11:50.398 --> 11:54.301
We've invited a new athlete to
join our do-gooding dream team.

11:54.336 --> 11:57.538
Please welcome fleet-footed
phenom, Bart Simpson.

11:57.572 --> 12:00.341
(crowd cheering)

12:00.375 --> 12:02.343
Hey, everyone.
I sure got a lot of attention

12:02.377 --> 12:04.545
for winning this year's
Race around the School.

12:04.579 --> 12:06.380
(crowd cheering)

12:06.414 --> 12:08.315
Completely deserved!

12:08.350 --> 12:09.783
Yeah, yeah. Thank you, Mel.

12:09.818 --> 12:12.219
But I am not here
to talk about myself.

12:12.254 --> 12:15.155
Milhouse, would you
join me at the podium?

12:15.190 --> 12:16.156
(clamoring)

12:16.191 --> 12:17.224
What's going on?

12:17.259 --> 12:18.792
Seriously, what-what's
transpiring?

12:18.827 --> 12:20.494
I've got to set things straight.

12:20.528 --> 12:22.997
During that same race, my friend
Milhouse was in the lead,

12:23.031 --> 12:25.666
when something
horrible happened!

12:27.369 --> 12:29.203
LISA:
<i>Bart knew the worst thing to do</i>

12:29.237 --> 12:31.372
<i>was pile lie upon lie.</i>

12:31.406 --> 12:33.407
<i>And that's exactly what he did.</i>

12:33.441 --> 12:34.909
Rather than try to figure
out what happened,

12:34.943 --> 12:36.477
Milhouse had the
courage to move on.

12:36.511 --> 12:38.312
To me, that's a hero.

12:38.346 --> 12:39.680
(crowd cheering)

12:39.714 --> 12:41.148
Nicely done.

12:41.182 --> 12:43.183
Now we will give out
free rubber bracelets.

12:43.218 --> 12:44.818
Do not wear them to bed.

12:44.853 --> 12:46.220
They smell like truck tires.

12:46.254 --> 12:47.421
They're disgusting.

12:51.559 --> 12:52.993
Crotch or forehead?

12:53.028 --> 12:55.195
Uh, forehead for once.

12:55.230 --> 12:57.598
Wha...?

13:08.209 --> 13:10.377
Bart Simpson!

13:10.412 --> 13:13.180
You ran away
when I was getting beat up!

13:13.214 --> 13:14.515
(crowd booing)

13:14.549 --> 13:15.749
Bart's a coward!

13:15.784 --> 13:16.951
He lied to us!

13:16.985 --> 13:19.420
Stop the tattoo!

13:19.454 --> 13:22.256
Uh, I could make it
a bag of groceries.

13:22.290 --> 13:24.391
All right, make sure there's
some French bread sticking out.

13:24.426 --> 13:27.428
Ow. Ow. Ow. Ow!

13:32.216 --> 13:34.384
[](crowd rabbling)

13:34.418 --> 13:37.287
Look how he runs now!

13:37.321 --> 13:38.955
LISA: <i>So Bart was revealed</i>
<i>as a coward.</i>

13:38.989 --> 13:42.191
<i>And now it seemed</i>
<i>like the whole world</i>

13:42.226 --> 13:43.860
<i>was against him.</i>

13:43.894 --> 13:44.861
(screams)

13:44.895 --> 13:47.030
(panting)

13:47.064 --> 13:49.365
MALE ANNOUNCER: Have you ever considered
a reverse-equity mortgage?

13:49.400 --> 13:51.401
That's what put
me in this dump!

13:51.435 --> 13:54.237
Grampa, everyone's
calling me a coward.

13:54.271 --> 13:56.105
Well, join the club.

13:56.140 --> 13:59.609
Anyone who makes it to old age
has got to be part-coward.

13:59.643 --> 14:01.945
Come on, you were
in World War II.

14:01.979 --> 14:04.347
Do you know
how I survived D-Day?

14:05.382 --> 14:07.317
(retches)

14:07.351 --> 14:09.786
Don't worry--
just a day at the beach.

14:13.991 --> 14:17.727
I'll be back around 1946!

14:17.761 --> 14:19.829
But don't people hate cowards?

14:19.863 --> 14:20.897
Sure do.

14:20.931 --> 14:22.665
But we outlive the brave.

14:22.700 --> 14:26.302
Leaving us cowards to make time
with the heroes' widows.

14:26.337 --> 14:29.205
After Korea,
I was drowning in boobies.

14:29.239 --> 14:31.774
Wow, that sounds pretty sweet.

14:31.809 --> 14:33.576
Well, there is a price.

14:33.611 --> 14:36.779
Do you wake up sweating
in the middle of the night?

14:36.814 --> 14:37.780
Yes.

14:37.815 --> 14:39.115
So do I.

14:39.149 --> 14:40.249
But I get back to sleep

14:40.284 --> 14:42.051
by counting the men I let down.

14:42.086 --> 14:44.621
There's Jerry, Izzy, Brooklyn,

14:44.655 --> 14:48.558
the O'Donnell boys,
the lost ship PT-108,

14:48.592 --> 14:50.560
the Poor Buggers
of Meatloaf Ridge,

14:50.594 --> 14:52.228
the Andrew sisters...

14:52.262 --> 14:54.163
(snoring)

14:57.267 --> 14:59.268
(gasps)

15:02.873 --> 15:04.007
I understand.

15:04.041 --> 15:06.509
You have standards.

15:06.543 --> 15:08.678
(gasps)

15:08.712 --> 15:11.147
This is an angry sleepover.

15:11.181 --> 15:13.883
I'm only doing it
'cause it was on the books.

15:15.152 --> 15:16.233
LISA
<i>While Bart was in hell,</i>

15:16.253 --> 15:17.553
<i>Homer was happily surrounded</i>

15:17.588 --> 15:19.756
<i>by fire and brimstone.</i>

15:19.790 --> 15:23.459
Okay, let's make some fireworks.

15:23.494 --> 15:25.828
Now drive slowly
and a-carefully

15:25.863 --> 15:27.797
to my workshop.

15:27.831 --> 15:31.034
It's in-a the Cobblestone
a-District.

15:34.705 --> 15:36.873
Oh, thank God--
a rickety bridge.

15:41.478 --> 15:42.979
Don't worry.

15:43.013 --> 15:46.049
We'll be safe
in the Gas a-Lamp a-District.

15:48.485 --> 15:50.887
(tires screeching)

15:55.893 --> 15:58.027
("Stars and Stripes Forever"
playing)

16:13.043 --> 16:14.177
Can I pitch something?

16:14.211 --> 16:15.278
Go ahead.

16:15.312 --> 16:16.779
Boom! Biddy bom-bom boom!

16:16.814 --> 16:18.614
Biddy bom bow! Ba-dip-boo!

16:18.649 --> 16:20.016
Boom! Boom!

16:20.050 --> 16:22.819
That's-a nice.
(laughs)

16:22.853 --> 16:25.521
♪ Sometimes when we touch ♪

16:25.556 --> 16:29.292
♪ The honesty's too much... ♪

16:31.161 --> 16:33.529
Wrong holiday, Charlie Brown.

16:34.965 --> 16:37.567
(overlapping chatter)

16:37.601 --> 16:39.368
Yoink. Ha-haw!

16:39.403 --> 16:40.903
We're on it, ma'am!

16:40.938 --> 16:43.406
Okay, coarse gunpowder,
get the ball in there,

16:43.440 --> 16:46.075
don't forget the wadding,
tamp, tamp, tamp,

16:46.110 --> 16:47.877
fine gunpowder in the pan,

16:47.911 --> 16:50.713
firing stance, take
careful aim and...

16:50.748 --> 16:52.014
(grunts)

16:52.049 --> 16:54.150
Uh, yeah,
not enough tamping, Chief.

16:54.184 --> 16:55.752
Coarse gunpowder,
ball, wadding,

16:55.786 --> 16:57.186
tamp, tamp, tamp,
tamp, tamp, tamp,

16:57.221 --> 16:58.821
fine gunpowder in the pan.

16:58.856 --> 16:59.956
Come on...

17:04.528 --> 17:07.096
Aw, my boy's having a bad night.

17:07.131 --> 17:08.698
We should get
this show on the road.

17:08.732 --> 17:10.833
No, the time is not yet right.

17:10.867 --> 17:13.502
When they look
at their watches and mutter,

17:13.537 --> 17:16.339
"Hey, when are these a-jerks
going to a-start?"

17:16.373 --> 17:19.842
That's when they're ready
to be enchanted.

17:19.877 --> 17:21.210
Come on, let's go!

17:21.244 --> 17:23.079
I can't stand to see
my family unhappy

17:23.113 --> 17:25.448
on America's holiest day.

17:25.482 --> 17:28.084
Actually, July 2 is

17:28.117 --> 17:31.053
when congress declared
independence,

17:31.088 --> 17:34.423
the date that-a
should be celebrated.

17:34.458 --> 17:35.758
Hey, Super Mario.

17:35.793 --> 17:38.027
Don't you tell me about America!

17:38.061 --> 17:39.896
Idiot! I'm-a right!

17:39.930 --> 17:41.197
No, you're a-wrong!

17:41.231 --> 17:43.933
"July 2"--
I am quoting John Adams!

17:43.967 --> 17:45.468
Who the hell is that?

17:45.502 --> 17:46.536
(both grunt)

17:46.570 --> 17:49.272
(all screaming)

17:49.306 --> 17:51.641
Oh, dear.
The term "target audience"

17:51.675 --> 17:54.343
is taking
on a sinister connotation.

17:58.582 --> 18:00.983
Milhouse, this is my chance
to make things right.

18:01.018 --> 18:03.219
What are you up to now?

18:03.253 --> 18:06.088
Get on that bus! I'll explain
during the explosions!

18:06.123 --> 18:08.090
Don't a-panic! We'll be okay

18:08.125 --> 18:11.227
as long as the sequence
doesn't a-start.

18:11.261 --> 18:13.830
Hit Bart's dad in the butt!

18:13.864 --> 18:15.231
Roger that.

18:15.265 --> 18:16.666
Did you factor in the wind?

18:16.700 --> 18:19.836
No.

18:19.870 --> 18:22.572
♪ Sometimes when we touch. ♪

18:22.606 --> 18:25.274
♪ The honesty's too much... ♪

18:25.309 --> 18:26.642
Don't worry, boys!

18:26.677 --> 18:29.178
I'll be with you
all the way to Berlin.

18:30.514 --> 18:32.481
(cackles)

18:32.516 --> 18:34.951
(all clamoring)

18:37.154 --> 18:39.121
(coughing)

18:39.156 --> 18:40.323
So, who is our hero?

18:40.357 --> 18:41.657
I hope it's Carl.

18:41.692 --> 18:43.259
Nah, no such luck.

18:43.293 --> 18:44.453
I was just Tweeting a picture

18:44.461 --> 18:46.329
of what I thought
was my last meal.

18:46.363 --> 18:48.297
Hot dog and French fries!

18:51.068 --> 18:52.401
(all gasping)

18:54.171 --> 18:57.340
Milhouse is our unlikely savior!

18:57.374 --> 19:00.543
MAN: Quit explaining everything,
let him talk.

19:00.577 --> 19:02.011
Well, it wasn't me.

19:02.045 --> 19:03.179
It was Bart who...

19:03.213 --> 19:05.214
Saw everything you did.

19:05.249 --> 19:07.016
Milhouse is the hero.

19:07.050 --> 19:09.952
Take it from me, the boy
who's lied throughout.

19:09.987 --> 19:12.622
ALL:
Milhouse! Milhouse!

19:12.656 --> 19:13.890
Oh, I get it now.

19:13.924 --> 19:16.559
Thanks, Bart.

19:16.593 --> 19:19.829
LISA: <i>So Milhouse got the redemption</i>
<i>he deserved,</i>

19:19.863 --> 19:22.732
<i>and so, in a way, did Bart.</i>

19:22.766 --> 19:25.468
ALL:
Coward! Coward! Coward!

19:25.502 --> 19:27.737
LISA:
<i>Which meant that, at long last,</i>

19:27.771 --> 19:30.973
<i>my brother could get</i>
<i>a good night's sleep.</i>

19:31.008 --> 19:33.609
(slow melody playing on piano)

19:40.350 --> 19:42.551
Oh, enough doom and gloom!

19:42.586 --> 19:44.954
(playing upbeat melody)

19:58.695 --> 20:00.829
[]Look, Maggie, I undid my deed.

20:00.863 --> 20:04.232
So I'm just gonna take
your feather and say good night.

20:04.267 --> 20:06.601
Oh, where are these coming from?

20:08.004 --> 20:09.571
Oh, I see.

20:09.605 --> 20:13.408
That's all you wanted.

20:13.443 --> 20:15.644
How's that, kiddo?

20:15.678 --> 20:17.412
(clucking)

