20:39.210 --> 20:40.276
HOMER (laughing):
<i>One more year, tops.</i>

20:40.311 --> 20:41.344
GIUSEPPE:
<i>I live-a longer than you.</i>

20:41.378 --> 20:43.513
<i>I take a senior spin class.</i>

20:43.547 --> 20:45.682
<i>Always I'm increasing</i>
<i>the tension.</i>

20:45.716 --> 20:46.783
HOMER:
<i>Then, burn on you</i>

20:46.817 --> 20:47.851
<i>'cause you'll be holding</i>

20:47.885 --> 20:48.952
<i>onto a dead guy.</i>
(laughs)

20:48.986 --> 20:51.121
GIUSEPPE:
♪ I wanna hold you ♪

20:51.155 --> 20:54.357
♪ A-till the fear
in me subsides... ♪

20:54.391 --> 20:55.458
HOMER:
<i>Believe me, if you're holding</i>

20:55.493 --> 20:57.594
<i>onto a 300-pound dead guy,</i>

20:57.628 --> 20:59.762
<i>fear is not gonna be</i>
<i>your problem.</i>

20:59.797 --> 21:01.931
GIUSEPPE: <i>Congratulations, you</i>
<i>have ruined a beautiful song.</i>

21:01.966 --> 21:04.100
HOMER: <i>It's a song?</i>
<i>I thought we were just riffing.</i>

21:04.135 --> 21:06.269
GIUSEPPE:
<i>I apologize to Dan Hill</i>

21:06.303 --> 21:07.337
<i>and all of our viewers.</i>

21:07.371 --> 21:08.805
HOMER: <i>I don't!</i>
Shh!

21:08.839 --> 21:11.792
<i>Usher, will you stop</i>
<i>that person who's shushing?</i>

